 :tx/rationale "Create task: LIVESTORE-5d: Migrate MCP server to LiveStore — the proto-daemon. CONTEXT: mcp.rs is a long-lived process (runs for the duration of an MCP connection). It has 18 call sites (11 load, 7 write) that each create their own DiskLayout + load_store. This is the most expensive redundancy in the codebase — each MCP tool call reloads the entire store. With LiveStore, the MCP server becomes the first daemon: one LiveStore created at startup, shared across all tool invocations. APPROACH: (1) Create LiveStore::open() in the MCP server startup (handle_initialize or before). (2) Store it in the MCP server state (McpState struct or equivalent). (3) All tool_xxx functions take &mut LiveStore instead of &DiskLayout. (4) tool_guidance, tool_query, tool_task_ready etc. use live.store(). (5) tool_transact, tool_task_go, tool_task_close, tool_task_create use live.write_tx(). (6) The append_guidance_footer helper uses live.store(). (7) The MCP server already runs as a long-lived process — it's literally the daemon pattern without the Unix socket. After this migration, adding a Unix socket for non-MCP clients is trivial. ACCEPTANCE: (A) One LiveStore::open() per MCP server lifetime. (B) All 18 call sites migrated. (C) MCP tool responses identical to pre-migration. (D) Second tool call in same session is measurably faster (no reload). (E) MCP server acts as proto-daemon for concurrent braid CLI calls. DEPENDS-ON: LIVESTORE-5a (dispatch pattern), LIVESTORE-6 (multi-agent awareness for detecting CLI writes). TRACES: ADR-FOUNDATION-034, ADR-FOUNDATION-031 (Introspective Observer). FILE: crates/braid/src/mcp.rs"
